    • Field Detail

      • TEXT_COMMON_SEPARATOR

        @Deprecated
public static final LocalizedObjectKey TEXT_COMMON_SEPARATOR
        Deprecated. 
        A common separator key for separating values. Defined in /com/i2rd/java/miwt/locale/common.l10n.xml This does not need to be localized. Also, the static key parsing removes the trailing space, and as a result provides limited utility.

      • setValues

        public void setValues(LocalizedText[] values)
        Set the values that are concatenated together. The arguments should be registered with a LocaleContext in order for the text to be updated on locale change. This object will not delegate locale changes to the values.
        Parameters:
        values - The values to set.

      • setValues

        public void setValues(LocalizedText[] values,
             LocalizedText separator)
        Set the values that are concatenated together using a separator. The arguments should be registered with a LocaleContext in order for the text to be updated on locale change. This object will not delegate locale changes to the values.
        Parameters:
        values - The values to set.
        separator - text to separate values in the array, can be null to use no separator.
        See Also:
        TEXT_SEPARATOR
